				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: best way to spend LDoN points<a name="45542"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 04 2:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The belt of grey flesh is a great waist slot item, I am currently using it until I can pickup something better. It comes with 2 slots one of which is type3 so you can aug a waist haste aug in it if you lack worn haste. The stat augs I feel your better off saving for the higher ones, +10 to any one stat isnt a huge bonus, there are a few +10 to multiple stats which would be more useful. The lifetap proc aug is not too high priority wise, I'd worry about fleshing out your worn gear before worrying about procs. IMO, the EC poison based damage augs are better all around than the lifetap augs.</span></td>
