			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: best way to spend LDoN points<a name="45553"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 11 04 3:02 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I wouldn't worry about any dex augs.  Dex, while nice, typically isn't a make or break point for anything.  How many times have you ever said &quot;man, if my xyz weapon would have proc'ed 1 more time we would have won!&quot;?  You probably haven't.  
<br />

<br />
I have looked at the belt of grey flesh myself.  A friend got the fabled mitheril twohander and passed his soulscream belt down, so I ended up not needing to get it.  
<br />

<br />
I would honestly recommend saving for the Everfrost 760 point cost armor set.  There are many items there that would probably be huge upgrades that will last you for a long time.  These pieces are similar to Ornate level gear.  I got the breastplate first and then slapped the chest only FT2 aug in it (think 360ish points for aug).  The other items in that armor set are equally nice.  
<br />

<br />
I'd recommend the armor set over belts since there seem to be more options for belts than for the main armor pieces.  Evenutally, you may want to get a haste belt and it would be a shame to have spent those 510 points at that point.  
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
